where they are present in public space, and where and how they carve out their private spaces. Through its unique exploration of the Russian example, this volume addresses the implications of the fragmented urban landscape on cultural practices and discourses, ethnicity, lifestyles and subcultures, and economic practices, and in doing so provides important insights applicable to a global context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCultural pluralismzRussia (Federation)xHistory. 0aImperialismxSocial aspectszRussia (Federation)xHistory. 0aLanguage and culturezRussia (Federation). 0aRationalization (Psychology)xPolitical aspectszRussia (Federation)xHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aAndreeva, Ulia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoltovskaya, Svetlana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrednikova, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDixon, Megan L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGdaniec, Cordula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGdaniec, Cordula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKosterina, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKosygina, Larisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarajeva, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScattone, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTkach, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184545831740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isb